               </form>
               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> (Lud.), <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረመየ፡</foreign> (sec. meum codicem) <subc>III,1</subc> (?) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> ici </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> ictu peti </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> ictu vulnerari </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">መለኮት፡</foreign> (<cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> divina Christi natura </quote></cit>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተቀሥፈ፡ ወኢሐመ። ተቀነወ፡ ወኢተሰቍረ። ተረግዘ፡ ወኢተረመየ፡</foreign> M.M. f. 115. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>taramya</quote></cit>, <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>taramaya</quote></cit> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረምየ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>taramya</quote></cit> <subc>III,1</subc> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይትረመይ፡</foreign> «<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>être cicatrisé</quote></cit>» ― <foreign xml:lang="am">ታተረ፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BNFabb217">BNFabb217</ref>, fol. 56v. <lb/>
 Antoine d’Abbadie dans son <bibl><ptr target="bm:Abbadie1881Dict"/><citedRange unit="page"> 516</citedRange></bibl> fait la remarque suivante: «Ces trois voix du verbe <foreign xml:lang="am">አተረ፡</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="am">ታተረ፡</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="am">አሳተረ፡</foreign>, sont données par J. d’Urbin pour traduire <foreign xml:lang="gez">ረመየ፡</foreign> , <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረምየ፡</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አርመየ፡</foreign>, dont la signification la plus connue est ‘blesser’ et non ‘cicatriser’. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርምየት፡</foreign> est traduit ensuite par <foreign xml:lang="gez">የሻረ፡ ቍስል፡</foreign>». Juste d’Urbin n’a pas dû faire un tel contresens. Peut-être a-t-il donné au mot «cicatrice» le sens de: «marque de blessure non fermée». <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 146</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረምየ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>taramya</quote></cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረመየ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>taramaya</quote></cit> pass. of <lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ረመየ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>ramaya</quote></cit>, (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 146</citedRange></bibl>) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>be sacrred</quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange unit="page"> 472a</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> </sense></entry>
